# Project 4 - Enable Full Automated Remediation

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to configure Full Automated Remediation for critical assets using Microsoft Defender for Endpoint.

---

## Objective

Configure Microsoft Defender to automatically investigate and remediate security threats without manual analyst intervention.

---

## Environment

| Item | Details |
|------|---------|
| Platform | Microsoft Defender for Endpoint |
| Operating System | Windows 11 |
| License | Microsoft Defender Trial |

---

## Prerequisites

- Global Administrator
- Device Group already created
- Onboarded devices

---

## Procedure

### Step 1

Login to Microsoft Defender Portal.

---

### Step 2

Navigate to

Settings

↓

Endpoints

↓

Permissions

↓

Device Groups

---

### Step 3

Select the Device Group.

---

### Step 4

Edit Device Group.

---

### Step 5

Configure Automation Level.

Select:

```
Full
```

---

### Step 6

Save the configuration.

---

## Verification

Confirmed that the Device Group now uses Full Automated Investigation and Remediation.

---

## Benefits

- Faster response
- Reduced manual work
- Automatic malware removal
- Automatic process termination
- Automatic file quarantine

